authorizeFunctions(address,uint64,(bytes.details: Authorizes the specified functions for the target and provided role.

createRole(string,uint64,uint32).details: Creates a new custom role for the calling instance. Custom roles are intended to be used for access control of custom components and its helper contracts. Custom roles are not intended to be used as target roles for custom contracts.

createTarget(address,string).details: Creates a new custom target. Custom targets are intended to be used for access control helper contracts of components. Custom targets are not intended to be used for components.

getInitialInfo().details: retuns the object info relevant for registering for this contract  IMPORTANT information returned by this function may only be used before the contract is registered in the registry. Once registered this information MUST only be accessed via the registry.

getRelease().details: Registers a registry contract for a specified chain. Only one chain registry may be registered per chain

grantRole(uint64,address).details: Grants the specified role to the account. Only active roles can be granted. Only instance owner or account with role admin role can call this function.

isActive().details: Returns true iff this contract managed by its authority is active. Queries the IAccessManaged.authority().

isConsumingScheduledOp().details: Returns true only in the context of a delayed restricted call, at the moment that the scheduled operation is being consumed. Prevents denial of service for delayed restricted calls in the case that the contract performs attacker controlled calls.

isInstanceLocked().details: returns the overall locking state of the instance (including all components)

isTargetLocked(address).details: returns the locking state of the specified target

linkToRegisteredNftId().details: links this contract to nft after registration

refillStakingRewardReserves(uint96).details: Refills the staking reward reserves for the specified target.

registerProduct(address,address).details: Register a product with the instance.

revokeRole(uint64,address).details: Revokes the specified role from the account. Only instance owner or account with role admin role can call this function.

setAuthority(address).details: Transfers control to a new authority. The caller must be the current authority.

setInstanceLocked(bool).details: Locks/unlocks the complete instance, including all its components.

setInstanceReader(address).details: Sets the instance reader for the instance. Permissioned: only the instance service may call this function.

setRoleActive(uint64,bool).details: Activates/deactivates the specified role. Only instance owner or account with role admin role can call this function.

setStakingLockingPeriod(uint40).details: Sets the duration for locking new stakes on this instance..

setStakingMaxAmount(uint96).details: Sets the maximum staked amount for this instance.

setStakingRewardRate(uint160).details: Sets the staking reward rate [apr] for this instance.

supportsInterface(bytes4).details: Returns true if this contract implements the interface defined by `interfaceId`. See the corresponding https://eips.ethereum.org/EIPS/eip-165#how-interfaces-are-identified[ERC section] to learn more about how these ids are created. This function call must use less than 30 000 gas.

unauthorizeFunctions(address,(bytes32,by.details: Removes any role authorization for the specified functions.

upgradeInstanceReader().details: Upgrades the instance reader to the specified target.

withdrawStakingRewardReserves(uint96).details: Defunds the staking reward reserves for the specified target.
